members.name: values
members.comment: Returns an array containing the constants of this enum class, in the order they are declared.

return: an array containing the constants of this enum class, in the order they are declared

members.name: valueOf
members.comment: Returns the enum constant of this class with the specified name. The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an enum constant in this class. (Extraneous whitespace characters are not permitted.)

param: name - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
throws: IllegalArgumentException - if this enum class has no constant with the specified name
NullPointerException - if the argument is null
return: the enum constant with the specified name

members.name: isClass
members.comment: Returns true if this is a kind of class: either CLASS or ENUM or RECORD.

return: true if this is a kind of class

members.name: isInterface
members.comment: Returns true if this is a kind of interface: either INTERFACE or ANNOTATION_TYPE.

return: true if this is a kind of interface

members.name: isField
members.comment: Returns true if this is a kind of field: either FIELD or ENUM_CONSTANT.

return: true if this is a kind of field

name: javax.lang.model.element.ElementKind
comment:
The kind of an element.

Note that it is possible additional element kinds will be added to accommodate new, currently unknown, language structures added to future versions of the Java programming language.
